column17: Comment something you liked or did not like about the procedural generation of the game (where the rooms, Dungeon map and enemies were generated).

Maps that generate more than three rooms offer no reward. Before the player chooses the next room, he should know where he goes, just like in the game Hades, where the symbol at the door indicates the destination. The premise is good, but some monsters are considered dead simply because they stop walking.
It was missing to generate the score in each expired stage ..
It was clearly noticeable the difficulty adjustment after each time the character died

I just understood that if I kept playing would appear new phases (after I died) after I came to answer the form and then I came back to play a little more, I think it was missing information or progress of the game.

The doors that led to rooms that had to defeat the enemies and return to the previous room were a nice touch, the fastest enemies shook the game, the scenarios with different obstacles, and the enemies with different attacks led to bump strategy to attack and defend themselves.
